From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 18:15:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: rockchip-host: Start link training at PERST# release

The known-good Rock Pi 4 / RK3399 path in Linux 6.1 enabled Gen1 link
training immediately before deasserting endpoint reset.  Linux 6.11 added
the PCIe-spec T_PVPERL wait to the Rockchip host driver, but placed that
wait after link training was enabled and before PERST# was deasserted:

        enable link training
        wait T_PVPERL
        deassert PERST#

On RK3399 this leaves the controller training while the endpoint is still
held in reset.  Keep the spec-mandated T_PVPERL delay, but perform it
before enabling link training.  This preserves the important Rock Pi 4
relationship from the working 6.1 path: link training is enabled
immediately before PERST# release.

The existing post-PERST# PCIE_RESET_CONFIG_WAIT_MS delay remains unchanged,
so PCI configuration still does not start until after the conventional
reset-to-config-request wait.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@local>
---
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
@@ -311,0 +312,2 @@ static int rockchip_pcie_host_init_port(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip)
+	msleep(PCIE_T_PVPERL_MS);
+
@@ -316,1 +318,0 @@ static int rockchip_pcie_host_init_port(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip)
-	msleep(PCIE_T_PVPERL_MS);
